references: A core part of ILE is the distance function that computes how close the loss values corresponding to different item groups are. The more similar the groups’ average losses are, the lower the distance would be. This is also consistent with the goal of the model, as it tries to minimize its overall loss values. As the groups’ item losses getting closer during the training process, the model’s predictions are more similar for different item groups, making the recommendation process more fair. Table 1 summarizes various distance functions that we experimented with in this paper.
